User Privacy Choices — Task Manager for iOS

Effective Date: March 17, 2026




Your Privacy, Your Control

At Task Manager for iOS, your privacy is our top priority. This page explains your privacy choices when using our app.




No Data Collection

Task Manager for iOS does not collect, store, or share any personal data. Because we collect nothing, there is no data to manage, delete, or opt out of.




No Tracking

We do not use any tracking technologies, advertising identifiers, or analytics tools. Your activity within the app is never monitored or recorded.




No Third-Party Sharing

Since no data is collected, no data is shared with third parties — including advertisers, analytics providers, or data brokers.




Your Choices

Because Task Manager for iOS operates with a zero-data-collection policy, you automatically have full privacy protection with no action required on your part. There are no settings to toggle, no consent forms to manage, and no accounts to delete.

